Patch for /etc/nsswitch.conf on the Buffalo NAS.

Removes winbind from passwd/group/shadow lookups.  winbindd is not started
in a standalone Samba setup; if winbind remains in nsswitch.conf, every
user/group lookup (including by smbd itself) tries to connect to the
winbind socket, which does not exist, causing repeated reconnect attempts
that pin one CPU core at ~100%.

Apply with:
    patch -p1 /etc/nsswitch.conf < nsswitch.conf.patch

--- a/etc/nsswitch.conf
+++ b/etc/nsswitch.conf
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 hosts:   files dns wins
-passwd:  files winbind
-group:   files winbind
-shadow:  files winbind
+passwd:  files
+group:   files
+shadow:  files
